  | No problem! I'm a junior dev so I'm like barely hanging with you here. However: I implemented this and it works really well. This is a way to condense two (or three or infinity) json+ld objects that could be page specific along with other more general structured data you may want to include on a page. The only thing I changed was returning an object instead of an array. I then collect these objects in the InjectSEO component to compile a json+ld array. This reads well and passes schema.org validation. Given that Next seems to do some "magic" in the Head to prevent having two separate tags and Google/others may not even pay attention to a second tag, this is the good stuff.<br>P.S. In the second snippet, it's also `getJSONStructuredData` instead of `getJSONStructruredData`, just in case anyone else finds their way here.<br>Thank you so much for your help. This is great. |
  
